
[1]caboose

   CABOOSE, n.

   1. The cook-room or kitchen of a ship. In smaller vessels, it is an
   inclosed fire-place, hearth or stove for cooking, on the main deck. In
   a ship of war, the cook room is called a galley.

   2. A box that covers the chimney in a ship.
